{"id":"2104.06590","submitter":"Yi Wang","authors":"Moon-Jin Kang, Alexis F. Vasseur, Yi Wang","title":"Time-asymptotic stability of composite waves of viscous shock and\n  rarefaction for barotropic Navier-Stokes equations","comments":"50 pages, some typos are corrected","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.AP math-ph math.DS math.MP","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We prove the time-asymptotic stability of composite waves consisting of the\nsuperposition of a viscous shock and a rarefaction for the one-dimensional\ncompressible barotropic Navier-Stokes equations. Our result solves a\nlong-standing problem first mentioned in 1986 by Matsumura and Nishihara in\n[25]. The same authors introduced it officially as an open problem in 1992 in\n[26] and it was again described as very challenging open problem in 2018 in the\nsurvey paper [23]. The main difficulty is due to the incompatibility of the\nstandard anti-derivative method, used to study the stability of viscous shocks,\nand the energy method used for the stability of rarefactions. Instead of the\nanti-derivative method, our proof uses the $a$-contraction with shifts theory\nrecently developed by two of the authors. This method is energy based, and can\nseamlessly handle the superposition of waves of different kinds.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 14 Apr 2021 02:24:38 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 25 Apr 2021 07:26:31 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 13 May 2021 06:40:30 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Fri, 15 Oct 2021 02:12:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-10-18"}
