milar to Borisov. ISOs originating from compact long-lived\nclusters would often show a deficiency in CO. As soon as a statistically\nsignificant sample of ISOs is discovered, the combined information of their\nobserved velocities and composition might help in constraining the dominant\nproduction process (abridged).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 14 Apr 2021 13:25:24 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-07-14"}
