 limit of 11.9\nweight percent). We also conclude that the observed bulk silicate Moon moment\nof inertia requires incomplete sinking of the IBC layer by mantle convection:\nonly 20 - 60 percent of the IBC material might have reached the core mantle\nboundary, while the rest either remained at the depth of origin or was mixed\ninto the middle mantle.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 14 Apr 2021 13:36:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-12-15"}
